<br>
The tactic is pretty simple.  Make a human Kensai with high Strength Constitution Dexterity and Intelligence.  Max him out, either by killing random stuff or by using the XP bug right before you enter Spellhold.  Dual him to mage and max him out again.  Give him a good robe and jewelry and have him dual wield Equalizer and Celestial Rage.  When you fight Drizzt use your melee characters to neutralize  the other members of his party, I recommend Keldorn and Minsc due to their high HP and Strength, as well as Keldorn's Holy Avenger.  Have your mage (I was using Imoen at this point) chain cast stone skin on your kensai.  Your cleric should be keeping the rest of the enemies silenced to prevent casting, and then should heal your melees.  Whatever fifth NPC you happen to be using should either melee, heal, or cast their most powerful debilitating spells, depending on class.  As your kensai/mage cast Improved Haste, and then use Kiai Shout.  If you keep stone skin up you'll be able to cut Drizzt down fairly fast, as long as you keep Stoneskin up.  Once Drizzt is down take out the rest of them at your leisure.  Summoned monsters and elementals are helpful, but if your party is already maxed out as they should be it won't be too hard except for Drizzt.  There's other ways to do this, but I prefer the full on whirlwind of death fashion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fenye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Reformed Mental Case</span><br>  Posts: 2081<br> <font color=#CC9900>(8/19/01 9:02:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mn.mediaone.net/timelord81/images/fenye.jpg hieght=285 width=129></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way I did it</span><hr size=1> xp bug? *perks up* what's this? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=le